This strategy is particularly effective in the cyber security space where most enterprises use multiple point solutions. An organization might have endpoint detection and response capabilities but lack comprehensive cloud security or identity and access management solutions. Install base targeting helps you identify these gaps and reach the right decision-maker with messaging that acknowledges their current investments while positioning your solution as a strategic addition that improves their overall security posture.

Intent Amplify's install base targeting capabilities use advanced technology intelligence to identify which companies use specific solutions, when they implemented them, and when they're most likely to be evaluating additional capabilities. This information helps your team move conversations past the "why should we replace our current solution" objection and focus instead on the business value and security improvements your offering provides.

